## Limitations

The primary limitation of this report is the reliance on secondary sources, which may not capture the full complexity of Stone Age life. Additionally, the interpretation of archaeological findings can vary, leading to different conclusions about the societal structures and technological advancements of the time. Furthermore, the lack of written records from the Stone Age means that much of the understanding is based on artifacts and remains, which can only provide a partial picture of the era.

